Python is a powerful, high-level programming language that is widely used in the DevOps field due to its simplicity and versatility.
Whether you're new to programming or looking to deepen your understanding of Python, 
grasping the basics is essential. In this blog, I'll cover fundamental Python topics that are crucial for DevOps engineers.

1. Variables and Data Types
Variables in Python are used to store information that can be referenced and manipulated later. 
Python supports several data types, including:

Integers: Whole numbers (e.g., 10, -3)
Floats: Decimal numbers (e.g., 3.14, -0.001)
Strings: Sequence of characters (e.g., "hello", 'world')
Booleans: Logical values (True or False)
